<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-648-004  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 648 004.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  June 1 1990 v29 n11 p123(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Processor board brings line-scan to PC/ATs. (Data Translation'sDT2856) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Andrews, Warren.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Data Translation introduces the DT2856 line-scan processor boardthat provides a complete interface from popular line-scan camerasto IBM PC ATs and compatibles while also handling lineacquisition, line storage, real-time processing and datacompression.andP;  The $3,995 board accommodates linear arrayresolution to 8,192 pixels per line and provides programmableacquisition rates between 20 kHz and 20 MHz.andP;  The DT2856 isintended for such applications as machine guidance, inspection,robotic vision, object recognition and motion analysis; its camerainterface is comprehensive yet easy to use.andP;  The camera controlsignals generated by the board conform to differential RS-422levels, and cameras are accommodated with or withoutsample-and-hold circuits.andP;  Correction circuitry is included tocompensate for variations in line-scan camera sensors, and anon-board analog-to-digital converter adjusts the input range tocorrect line-to-line variations in signal levels to track incomingsignal levels automatically.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data Translation Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DATX.andO;Product:   Data Translation DT2856 (Graphics board) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCamerasInterfaceMicrocomputersComputer VisionObject RecognitionGraphics Boards-CardsImage Processing.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>